    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Manipal Digital Health Holdings Services. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Software Engineer to strengthen our Delhi-based team.\n\nAbout Manipal Digital Health Holdings Services:\nManipal Digital Health Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Write and execute unit tests and integration tests\n• Work with agile methodologies including daily stand-ups and sprint planning\n• Collaborate with cross-functional teams including product, design, and QA\n• Mentor junior developers and conduct knowledge-sharing sessions\n• Contribute to system architecture and technical design decisions\n• Participate in code reviews and contribute to technical discussions\n• Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in TensorFlow\n• Proficiency in Kubernetes\n• Proficiency in MongoDB\n• Proficiency in React\n• Proficiency in Node.js\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Rust\n• Proficiency in Java\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Delhi, Delhi, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Manipal Digital Health Holdings Services!",
